features: KEEP YOUR AIR FRYER CLEAN: No holes & specially designed with the side to prevent any food residues or grease from sticking or flowing to your air fryer bottom, and keep sides & bottom of air fryer almost spotless, basically no cleanup after baking. Meanwhile no affect on the hot air circulation in air fryer.
PREMIUM RECTANGLE AIR FRYER PAPER LINER: Made from 100% food grade pulp with food grade nonstick coating, healthy, nonstick, grease-proof, waterproof, non-absorbent, 100% safe for daily use.

DUAL AIR FRYER PARCHMENT PAPER: 8.6*5.5inch inner diameter & 12.2*8.8inch unfold diameter, height: 1.7inch, perfect for most dual zone air fryer on the market, including ninja dual air fryer DZ090/DZ201/DZ401, Chefman, ULTICOR, Power XL double air fryer and more.

HEAT RESISTANCE: Heat safe up to 450 degree F (232℃), microwave and oven safe, perfect air fryer accessories. WARNING: PLACE ENOUGH FOOD on the top of the liners to avoid having them fly away or get burned by the heating element!

WIDE USES: These ninja air fryer liners can be used for baking or cooking various of food, such as chips, chicken, cakes, seafood, steak, meat and more, perfect for home/outdoor cooking, baking, camping and party, etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars They don't work too well with my ninja dual air fryer, burning inside of air fryer.
reviews.reviewText: Purchased these specifically because I saw that they would fit in my ninja dual air fryer. I just got it as an "upgrade" to my older yedi air fryer. I previously used a different brand of parchment paper baskets in that one but they don't fit in here so I bought these instead. However, these don't fit well either. They are too tall slightly so that they have issues with burning on the tops of them, I have to either trim them slightly before use or fold them down and hope that they stay that way during the cooking process. Other than that issue they are fine but the burning is a bit concerning. The first time using them there was some smoke in the air fryer as well. I had food on them and did not put them in during the preheat portion. they were only in the air fryer for around 15 minutes to make sweet potato fries and this was with shaking them halfway through too.
